Key Match Events: Bolivia claimed their second win in the South American World Cup qualifiers with a 4-0 home victory over Venezuela.
Ramiro Vaca scored the first goal for Bolivia at the 13th minute.
Carmelo Algarañaz scored a penalty at the 45'+5' minute.
Miguel Terceros scored at the 46th minute.
Enzo Monteiro scored the final goal at the 89th minute.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at one of the world's highest altitude stadiums in El Alto, La Paz, Bolivia.
